ernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":1,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":10,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Joan FitzRichard was born in 1327, in Hoveringham, Nottinghamshire, England, her father, Richard De Nottingham, was 28 and her mother, Mrs Elizabeth De Nottingham, was 27. She married Nicholas Goushill before 1350, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1362, in her hometown, at the age of 35."},"et":{"1327–1362":"1327–1362","1316–1393":"1316–1393","1350–1374":"1350–1374","1353–1402":"1353–1402","1355–1403":"1355–1403","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1374":"1374","1362":"1362","1350":"1350","1393":"1393","1327":"1327","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1403":"1403","1402":"1402","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","1453":"1453","1353":"1353","before 1350":"enne 1350","about 1353":"umbes 1353","about 1350":"umbes 1350","1328":"1328","England":"England","Hoveringham, Nottinghamshire, England":"Hoveringham, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1327–1362":"1327–1362","1316–1393":"1316–1393","1350–1374":"1350–1374","1353–1402":"1353–1402","1355–1403":"1355–1403","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1374":"1374","1362":"1362","1350":"1350","1393":"1393","1327":"1327","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1403":"1403","1402":"1402","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","1453":"1453","1353":"1353","before 1350":"ennen vuotta 1350","about 1353":"noin 1353","about 1350":"noin 1350","1328":"1328","England":"England","Hoveringham, Nottinghamshire, England":"Hoveringham, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fr":{"1327–1362":"1327–1362","1316–1393":"1316–1393","1350–1374":"1350–1374","1353–1402":"1353–1402","1355–1403":"1355–1403","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1300–Female":"1300–Décédée","1374":"1374","1362":"1362","1350":"1350","1393":"1393","1327":"1327","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1403":"1403","1402":"1402","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","1453":"1453","1353":"1353","before 1350":"avant 1350","about 1353":"environ 1353","about 1350":"environ 1350","1328":"1328","England":"Angleterre","Hoveringham, Nottinghamshire, England":"Hoveringham, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Joan FitzRichard est née en 1